Just put "next;" before you use select()/prompt()/menu; 

(up to a reasonable limit so scrolling isn't necessary, or at least kept to a minimum) 
makes the "conversation" flow, like the player and NPC are having an actual conversation. 
But, that's just my personal preference at least.


Exemple :

mes "Que nivel de jugador tienes?";
next;
if(select("Usuario Experto:Principiante")==1) {
 cutin "jpn_anni02",2;
 mes "^9933ff[Rates]^000000";
 mes "^A0A0A0~Usa el comando @rates^000000";
 mes "^9933ff[Cartas MVPs]^000000";
